<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 7:29PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN MIFFLIN AND WEST
CENTRAL JUNIATA COUNTIES THROUGH 745 PM EDT...
At 729 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Huntingdon, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Strodes Mills, Blacklog, McVeytown, Longfellow, Newton Hamilton and
Atkinson Mills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
